 {"id": "franken_networkx-nbunchseq", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] cut_size/edge_boundary/etc TypeErrored when nbunch was a set", "description": "fnx cut_size/normalized_cut_size/edge_boundary/node_boundary threw TypeError when S/T/nbunch1/nbunch2 was a set, dict_keys, generator, or other non-Sequence iterable. nx accepts any iterable. Added _coerce_nbunch helper that lists-materialises non-tuple/list input. edge_expansion(G, S={0,1,2,3}) and similar composition chains now work.", "status": "closed", "priority": 3, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:46:21.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:46:21.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:46:21.000000000Z", "close_reason": "_coerce_nbunch helper", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-mutiter", "title": "REVIEW: [LOW] mutation during nodes() iteration silently allowed while nx raises RuntimeError", "description": "fnx.Graph.nodes() returns a list (snapshot); nx returns a dict view that detects concurrent modification. User code mutating during iteration gets silent behavior on fnx but clear RuntimeError on nx. Queued \u2014 a full fix requires changing the iteration contract which is a deeper architectural change.", "status": "closed", "priority": 4, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:46:21.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:55:38Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:55:38Z", "close_reason": "Graph and DiGraph node view iterators now raise RuntimeError when the node set changes during iteration.", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-mutiterfix", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] mutation during NodeView iteration now detected \u2014 matches nx RuntimeError", "description": "Previously queued in br-mutiter: fnx.Graph.nodes() iteration did not detect mid-iteration mutation; nx raises RuntimeError. Fix: monkey-patch __iter__ on NodeView/DiNodeView/MultiGraphNodeView/MultiDiGraphNodeView to snapshot len(self) at iter() time and check each yield. On mismatch, raise RuntimeError with nx-exact wording. Unblocked existing test_nodes_iteration_detects_node_set_mutation[Graph-Graph] + [DiGraph-DiGraph] tests.", "status": "closed", "priority": 3, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:56:43.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:56:43.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:56:43.000000000Z", "close_reason": "__iter__ wrapper with size-snapshot check", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-tcmg", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] transitive_closure broken for multigraphs + cyclic DiGraphs + undirected", "description": "fnx.transitive_closure had 3 real parity bugs: (1) on MultiDiGraph input it downgraded the class to DiGraph, losing parallel-edge preservation; (2) on cyclic DiGraphs it omitted self-loops (u,u) that nx adds when u participates in a cycle (reachable from itself via a path of length >= 1); (3) on undirected graphs it raised NetworkXNotImplemented while nx handles them. Fixed by delegating to nx for multigraphs, undirected, cyclic-directed, and reflexive=True cases; Rust fast-path retained for acyclic DiGraphs where all three defects do not apply.", "status": "closed", "priority": 2, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:59:43.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:59:43.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:59:43.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Delegate for multigraph/undirected/cyclic/reflexive; Rust fast-path for acyclic DiGraph only", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
